		"title"		: "Harry the Dirty Dog",
		"text"		: "1\n00:00:01,720 --> 00:00:07,140\nWelcome to Storyline Online, brought to you by the Screen Actors Guild Foundation.\n\n2\n00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:10,580\nI'm Betty White, and I think we're going to have a good time today!\n\n3\n00:00:10,580 --> 00:00:16,080\nAt least I know I am. I'm going to be reading you a book, okay.\n\n4\n00:00:16,090 --> 00:00:21,240\nI love animals, all animals, but maybe dogs in particular.\n\n5\n00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:26,789\nSo today, I'm going to be reading you a story about Harry the Dirty Dog.\n\n6\n00:00:26,789 --> 00:00:32,009\nIt's by Gene Zion, pictures by Margaret Bloy Graham.\n\n7\n00:00:32,009 --> 00:00:36,980\nHarry was a white dog with black spots who liked everything,\n\n8\n00:00:36,980 --> 00:00:39,320\nexcept getting a bath.\n\n9\n00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:43,140\nSo, one day, when he heard the \nwater running in the tub,\n\n10\n00:00:44,060 --> 00:00:49,060\nhe took the scrubbing brush... and buried it in the backyard.\n\n11\n00:00:50,740 --> 00:00:53,520\nThen he ran away from home.\n\n12\n00:00:54,580 --> 00:01:00,320\nHe played where they were fixing the street and got very dirty.\n\n13\n00:01:02,180 --> 00:01:05,960\nHe played at the railroad and got even dirtier.\n\n14\n00:01:07,420 --> 00:01:12,620\nHe played tag with other dogs and became dirtier still.\n\n15\n00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:18,290\nHe slid down a coal chute and got the dirtiest of all.\n\n16\n00:01:18,290 --> 00:01:26,060\nIn fact, he changed from a white dog with black spots to a black dog with white spots.\n\n17\n00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:37,900\nAlthough there were many other things to do, Harry began to wonder if his family thought that he had really run away.\n\n18\n00:01:40,020 --> 00:01:48,060\nHe felt tired and hungry too, so without stopping on the way, he ran back home.\n\n19\n00:01:49,540 --> 00:01:55,840\nWhen Harry got to his house, he crawled through the fence \nand sat looking at the back door.\n\n20\n00:01:56,740 --> 00:02:02,220\nOne of the family looked out and said, \"There's a strange dog in the backyard...\n\n21\n00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:05,040\nBy the way, has anyone seen Harry?\"\n\n22\n00:02:07,310 --> 00:02:13,180\nWhen Harry heard this, he tried very hard to show them he was Harry.\n\n23\n00:02:13,180 --> 00:02:20,680\nHe started to do all his old, clever tricks. He flip-flopped and he flop-flipped.\n\n24\n00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:23,440\nHe rolled over and played dead.\n\n25\n00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:26,480\nHe danced and he sang.\n\n26\n00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:32,740\nHe did these tricks over and over again, but everyone shook their heads and said,\n\n27\n00:02:32,740 --> 00:02:35,360\n\"Oh no, it couldn't be Harry.\"\n\n28\n00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:46,400\nHarry gave up and walked slowly toward the gate, but suddenly he stopped.\n\n29\n00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:51,240\nHe ran to a corner of the garden and started to dig furiously.\n\n30\n00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:57,640\nSoon he jumped away from the hole barking short, happy barks.\n\n31\n00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,940\nHe'd found the scrubbing brush!\n\n32\n00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:03,580\nAnd carrying it in his mouth, he ran into the house.\n\n33\n00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:07,560\nUp the stairs he dashed, \nwith the family following close behind.\n\n34\n00:03:08,540 --> 00:03:14,749\nHe jumped into the bathtub and sat up begging, with the scrubbing brush in his mouth,\n\n35\n00:03:14,749 --> 00:03:17,680\na trick he certainly had never done before.\n\n36\n00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:21,700\n\"This little doggy wants a bath!\" cried the little girl,\n\n37\n00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:25,680\nand her father said, \"Why don't you and your brother give him one?\"\n\n38\n00:03:26,620 --> 00:03:33,140\nHarry's bath was the soapiest one he'd ever had. It worked like magic.\n\n39\n00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:37,880\nAs soon as the children started to scrub, they began shouting,\n\n40\n00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:42,440\n\"Mummy! Daddy! Look, look! Come quick!\n\n41\n00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:46,959\nIt's Harry! It's Harry! It's Harry!\" they cried.\n\n42\n00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:51,800\nHarry wagged his tail and was very, very happy.\n\n43\n00:03:51,800 --> 00:04:01,760\nHis family combed and brushed him lovingly, and he became once again a white dog with black spots.\n\n44\n00:04:03,420 --> 00:04:07,029\nIt was wonderful to be home.\n\n45\n00:04:07,029 --> 00:04:11,339\nAfter dinner, Harry fell asleep in his favorite place,\n\n46\n00:04:11,339 --> 00:04:16,299\nhappily dreaming of how much fun it had been getting dirty.\n\n47\n00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:24,500\nHe slept so soundly, he didn't even feel the scrubbing brush he'd hidden under his pillow.\n\n48\n00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:32,780\nDid you like that? \nWell you're going to like this even better.\n\n49\n00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:34,040\nThis is my friend Ringo.\n\n50\n00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:39,500\nI just met him, but he's a shelter puppy who found a wonderful forever home,\n\n51\n00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:47,740\nso he has a happy ending just as Harry the Dirty Dog had a happy ending. Thank you.",
		"avatarURL"	: "https://www.storylineonline.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/HarryTheDirtyDog.jpg",
