		"title"		: "The Kiss That Missed",
		"text"		: "1\n00:00:02,300 --> 00:00:04,000\nHey guys!  I'm Karan Brar.\n\n2\n00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,000\nWelcome to the SAG Foundation's Storyline Online\n\n3\n00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:12,000\nToday we're reading The Kiss That Missed\nwritten and illustrated by David Melling.\n\n4\n00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:22,040\nOnce upon a Tuesday the King was in a hurry as usual.\n\n5\n00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:28,000\n\"Goodnight,\" he said and blew his son a royal kiss.\n\n6\n00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:32,280\nIt missed.\n\n7\n00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:36,120\nThe young prince watched it rattle around the room,\n\n8\n00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:41,060\nthen bounce out of the window and into the night.\n\n9\n00:00:41,060 --> 00:00:43,400\nThe prince told the Queen.\n\n10\n00:00:44,460 --> 00:00:46,460\nThe Queen told the King,\n\n11\n00:00:46,460 --> 00:00:51,600\nand the King had a quick word with his loyal Knight.\n\n12\n00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:54,620\n\"Follow that Kiss!\" he squawked.\n\n13\n00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:57,780\nThe Knight mounted his horse...\n\n14\n00:00:57,780 --> 00:00:59,640\nEventually ...\n\n15\n00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:13,960\nand galloped off in hot pursuit until they came to the wild wood.\n\n16\n00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:17,340\nWild creatures with wild eyes,\n\n17\n00:01:17,340 --> 00:01:22,020\ntoo much hair, and very bad manners lived here.\n\n18\n00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:28,240\nIt was dark.  It was smelly.  It was ...\n\n19\n00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:32,100\n...snowing.\n\n20\n00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:35,270\nThey were not alone.\n\n21\n00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:41,420\nThere were bears with long claws and growly roars,\n\n22\n00:01:41,660 --> 00:01:45,720\nswooping owls of all shapes and sizes,\n\n23\n00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:50,940\nand a pack of hungry wolves with dribbly mouths.\n\n24\n00:01:51,799 --> 00:01:54,900\n\"EEK!\" squeaked the Knight.\n\n25\n00:01:54,900 --> 00:01:56,700\nAnd then, suddenly ...\n\n26\n00:01:56,800 --> 00:02:00,460\n...with a sparkle the Royal Kiss came floating by and,\n\n27\n00:02:00,460 --> 00:02:03,820\nin turn, said goodnight to everyone.\n\n28\n00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:06,660\nBears stopped being growly,\n\n29\n00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:10,500\nOwls stopped being swoopy,\n\n30\n00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,680\nWolves stopped being dribbly,\n\n31\n00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:16,360\nAnd before you could say \"Follow that kiss!\"\n\n32\n00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:21,560\nThey all settled down for a good night's sleep.\n\n33\n00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:28,360\nAfter a while they sat down on a wrinkly old tree trunk to rest.\n\n34\n00:02:28,820 --> 00:02:31,860\nThe wrinkly old tree trunk twitched...\n\n35\n00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:36,080\nand slowly rose into the air...\n\n36\n00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:39,400\nabove the woods and into the clouds.\n\n37\n00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:45,020\nAt last they found themselves staring into a pair of very hairy nostrils.\n\n38\n00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:51,180\nA dragon with \"this-pair-would-be-nice-on-toast\" eyes\nleered greedily at them.\n\n39\n00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:57,140\nSuddenly...\nwith a sparkle the Royal Kiss came floating by\n\n40\n00:02:57,140 --> 00:03:00,740\nand flew right up the dragon's nose.\n\n41\n00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:06,040\nHe sat up, sniffed, and blinked.\n\n42\n00:03:06,220 --> 00:03:11,220\nSlowly, he opened his mouth, took a deep breath, and...\n\n43\n00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:14,260\nSneezed!\n\n44\n00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:18,080\n\"Hang on!\" he said as they tumbled through the trees.\n\n45\n00:03:18,260 --> 00:03:22,260\n\"Come back!\" he puffed as he lumbered after them.\n\n46\n00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:25,720\n\"I want to pick you up and...\n\n47\n00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:31,080\nkiss you goodnight.\"\n\n48\n00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:37,320\nSlowly they all made their way back to the castle.\n\n49\n00:03:38,740 --> 00:03:42,480\nThat night the prince was happy,\n\n50\n00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,940\nthe Queen was happy,\n\n51\n00:03:44,940 --> 00:03:49,480\nand the King promised to stop always being in a hurry.\n\n52\n00:03:51,660 --> 00:03:54,300\nHe made sure everyone was comfortable\n\n53\n00:03:54,520 --> 00:04:00,680\nand slowly read them a bedtime story from beginning to end...\n\n54\n00:04:03,950 --> 00:04:05,950\nalmost.\n\n55\n00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:14,190\nThe end. I'm Karan Brar again \nand thank you guys for checking out Storyline Online.\n\n56\n00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:15,810\nSee ya!",
